ws/6159|work=Polish Olympic Committee|accessdate=2013年11月7日|archive-date=2013年11月11日|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111162226/http://www.pkol.pl/pl/pages/news/6159|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1016844/poland-and-slovakia-confirm-joint-bid-for-2022-winter-olympics-and-paralympics|title=Poland and Slovakia confirm joint bid for 2022 Winter Olympics and Paralympics|website=www.insidethegames.biz|accessdate=2019-09-05|archive-date=2020-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201206132307/https://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1016844/poland-and-slovakia-confirm-joint-bid-for-2022-winter-olympics-and-paralympics|dead-url=no}}</ref>，[[烏克蘭|烏克蘭]][[利沃夫|利沃夫]]于2014年6月退-{}-出申办<ref name=lvivoff>{{cite web|title=Lviv Officially Bids For 2022 Winter Olympics|url=http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/winter_olympic_bids/future_winter_bids/1216136800.html|work=GamesBids.com|accessdate=2013年11月5日|archive-date=2013年11月5日|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105183155/http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/winter_olympic_bids/future_winter_bids/1216136800.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，使申办城市减少为三个。

